Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.66,0:00:14.44,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kono sora no kagayaki kimi no mune ni todoiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.66,0:00:14.44,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}The luminance of the sky has reached your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.65,0:00:24.47,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}yumemiteta shirabe wa shizukesa no youni
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.65,0:00:24.47,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}The melody I dreamed of was like silence.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.34,0:00:29.52,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kimi no te ga mada yume ni tookutemo
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.34,0:00:29.52,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Even if your hand is still far away in my dreams,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.36,0:00:34.58,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}omoidashiteyou yasashii koe wo
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.36,0:00:34.58,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}I’ll still remember your kind voice
Dialogue: 3,0:00:34.34,0:00:47.37,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}dareka ga kimi no tame utatta shiawase no koto
Dialogue: 3,0:00:34.34,0:00:47.37,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}and the happiness that was sung for you.
Dialogue: 4,0:00:47.11,0:00:56.77,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}sora no woto hibike takaku kanashimi wo koete
Dialogue: 4,0:00:47.11,0:00:56.77,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Let the sound of the sky ring high over your sadness.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:56.54,0:01:07.32,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kimi no me ni utsuru mono wa subete hontou no sekai
Dialogue: 5,0:00:56.54,0:01:07.32,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Everything reflected in your eyes is that of the real world.
Dialogue: 6,0:01:07.15,0:01:16.79,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}namida sae kimi wo koko ni todomete okenai
Dialogue: 6,0:01:07.15,0:01:16.79,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Even tears won’t be able to stop you here.
Dialogue: 7,0:01:16.52,0:01:28.92,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}furisosogu hikari no naka ashita wo kanadete
Dialogue: 7,0:01:16.52,0:01:28.92,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Amidst the descending lights, you’ll play the song of tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.32,0:01:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready, my ladies?{well... soldiers...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.93,0:01:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.61,0:01:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.02,0:01:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Advancing!{these lines match ep5}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.78,0:01:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are our allies?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.80,0:01:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,40 degrees to the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.12,0:01:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready main cannon!{Matches 05}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.07,0:01:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Distance, 400!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.07,0:01:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Load H.E.A.T. round!{High Explosive, Anti-Tank, for those interested}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.18,0:01:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.95,0:02:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olga?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.00,0:02:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been canned up in here for three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.06,0:02:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not dying until I get a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.70,0:02:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Target sighted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.97,0:02:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.14,0:02:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, inform the rear guard.{Matches 5}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.35,0:02:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One enemy unit neutralized. Advance to our flanks.{These lines mostly differ in formality between the ones in ep 5, though this one is a tad different, thus the change.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.52,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.41,0:02:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia, cover Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's flashing, it's not thunder, so calm down.{...wouldn't that make you MORE panicked..? >_>}{She's only freaked out by thunder.. at least until she sees the trumpetarm, haha}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.50,0:02:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.96,0:02:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F-From 3 o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.15,0:03:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.95,0:03:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Anna!{Maybe just use Lieutenant here.. but this is the technical term}{I think that 2nd Lts. generally are referred to as "Lt." unless there's an actual Lt. nearby (probably because it's easier to say). Plus, in this panicky situation, it's better to be shorter I think. Plus, we've been using the long form...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.89,0:03:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper supplies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.72,0:03:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bamboo supplies...{Approximation, as I've never heard this term before, but it's paper + bamboo to make the lanterns.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:18.59,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,89.333333)}The Chirping Crickets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:18.59,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,416)}Offerings for the Deceased
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.92,0:04:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Noël!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't press it down firmly, it won't get clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.12,0:04:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.46,0:04:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too cold in the winter, but since this building is also cool in the summer, it's a real lifesaver right now.{Can play with this line to make it sound better.. they do say 'saved', but this is the best I could come up with}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.83,0:04:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wasn't it Rio-senpai and the Commander's turn to do the laundry today?{-tachi... bleh. It's too bad no one actually says "rio-senpai et al" in English. I changed "Felicia-san" to the "Captain" partly because it's jarring to put in names that you don't hear. Fewer people would realize she doesn't say Captain either. I'd put "their", but it seems too short, and it may not be obvious she's referring to Rio-senpai and the Captain.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.37,0:05:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were busy or something and asked us to switch with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.68,0:05:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.34,0:05:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, she said she wasn't hungry and told us to eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll have some!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.07,0:05:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that? Getting ready for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you play around with the food, you'll get cursed{FACE DIVINE WRATH! Man I'm so screwed for all the food I played with}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.91,0:05:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not playing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.45,0:05:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time for Obon, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.98,0:05:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck is "Obon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fiesta du Lumières.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.99,0:05:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fie...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fiesta du Lumières is an event specific to Southern Helvetia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.63,0:05:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to their folklore, the souls of the departed return to the Earth for a short time during the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.05,0:05:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to commune with these spirits again,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.62,0:05:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lanterns are set adrift on a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the countryside, this festival is often called "Obon."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.99,0:05:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.19,0:05:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Then it's the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.34,0:06:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The souls of the departed come back...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Hold it, hold it! What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.89,0:06:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that ghosts actually come back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper lanterns? That sounds so wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.35,0:06:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back home in the country, we only lit lamps.{Countryside is more formal and is suited for Noel talk, but this is Kanata (and i missed out on "country" in ep 6 >_>), so I'll just use "country" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.95,0:06:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When people go to heaven, they stay there forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.93,0:06:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things that wander around on the Earth are bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.23,0:06:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.52,0:06:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Come give us a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.75,0:06:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you two go shopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.51,0:06:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Those are...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.30,0:06:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They looked good, so we bought some.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, these as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.92,0:06:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong, Father. It's like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.11,0:06:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother and father?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.96,0:07:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! It's very well made.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.06,0:07:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Even the Church approved it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.69,0:07:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Fie– whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. If we were in the central region, there would have been an uproar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.01,0:07:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where I come from, we make horses and cows out of cucumbers and eggplants
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.83,0:07:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to act as mounts for our ancestors.{Vote we keep this line for beastiality. MOUNT THEM COWS, MEN!}{Maybe if it was grammatical, i'd keep it :P}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, we all dance to entertain the ancestors who returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.86,0:07:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, you're both making them as well?{Heh, she says senpai-tachi, but that's hard to write in english. i suppose this way works around this...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.84,0:07:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Last year we just watched, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our job to observe{lit:survey} and join in with the local inhabitants to smooth over relations.{lit: smooth concerns}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.97,0:08:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't get too hung up over it, it's just a normal festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Filicia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.79,0:09:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm fine. I just made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.37,0:09:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it sure is rare for the Commander to be that clumsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.54,0:09:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.91,0:09:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been rather hot for the past few days, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.21,0:09:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been able to sleep well{much?}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.99,0:09:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to take a short break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.21,0:09:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.15,0:10:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Commander sure is acting strangely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.18,0:10:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, it seems she didn't finish her lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, she ignored our food expenses and bought watermelons and other things.{A bit of a troubled sentence, perhaps you can massage it a bit}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a lot going on, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.74,0:10:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, I should really...{Not much here to work with.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.62,0:10:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.42,0:10:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has times when they don't want to talk to anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just let her be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.04,0:10:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noël?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.55,0:10:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know, Rio?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.38,0:10:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I read the records.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.92,0:10:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was there in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your arm steady, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.96,0:11:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.18,0:11:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, a monster that looked like the Commander came out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.73,0:11:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say that a lot of things used to live in this ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who caused the world to slowly come to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.47,0:11:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was we humans who completely destroyed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.05,0:11:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's... just a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.10,0:11:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.52,0:11:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then for what reason are we fighting?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.59,0:12:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.74,0:12:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ideograms...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.09,0:12:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.42,0:12:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be great if I could read your last words, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This equipment...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.78,0:12:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be... from the previous age?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Olga...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Martina...{Maybe Marlina? Check vs ~19:25, and see what you think. Looks like an L to me, though sounds like a T.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.87,0:13:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... am I the only one...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.98,0:13:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... there are people who still live in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.32,0:13:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.98,0:13:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you apologizing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.42,0:13:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because we lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.62,0:13:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.03,0:14:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't able to protect you.{Actually says protect, but this works better if you keep the pause between.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.06,0:14:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.49,0:14:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world has already ended.{uses a final form here, trying to carry it over.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are just the dregs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the final remnants of humanity we had left behind.{could also be translated as "the last remaining humans of the froth that was scooped/ladeled out" - N:More precisely he's saying the last bubbles of humanity. You could use that, or move it into "pockets" if you so felt.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.03,0:14:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity can...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.16,0:14:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This world can no longer return to its former prosperity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.21,0:14:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't decide that on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.71,0:14:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's fine for it to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.50,0:15:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This shell{remainder} of a world, which is living in the depths{overflowing} of despair, is just too sad, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.79,0:15:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Is there any meaning to living in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.80,0:15:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me...{??}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.50,0:15:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.71,0:15:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you, please save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.33,0:16:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my unit{platoon?} had arrived just half a day earlier, I'm sure this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Iliya...{She more or less say crown princess, but that might be a bit much}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.47,0:16:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was a little surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.60,0:16:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you ignored the Fiesta du Lumières last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the change of heart?{Literal is "change of mind" but it's not very english}{I could have gone "why did you change your mind", but this phrase is better}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.12,0:16:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a nice color, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it from that old man earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:16:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.64,0:17:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.51,0:17:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.15,0:17:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, that person was everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like her, this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its people were the ones I'd wanted to protect.{This is hard to represent. She's saying 'this country' then trails off, and picks back up with people instead. I couldn't find a good way to make it flow, so Nazo, counting on you =D}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.08,0:17:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But every now and then, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.13,0:17:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What point is there in doing that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.65,0:17:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, if she were to actually return...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.10,0:17:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would want her to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More so, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.65,0:17:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.65,0:17:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might have made them feel a bit uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a requirement for a commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.22,0:17:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even I... that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.36,0:17:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways! You don't have to suffer alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.19,0:17:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even I can listen, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.25,0:17:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Rio.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll take you up on your offer and fill you in.{perhaps use 'fill you in' to make it sound more.. cunning, like she's saying =D}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.03,0:18:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.47,0:18:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about the summer fat.{?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.66,0:18:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I won't be able to wear winter clothing.{?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.45,0:18:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd heard that eating watermelon would make you thinner, so I thought I'd try it out, but...{wait, where did this come from... XD}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.10,0:18:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what's wrong, Rio?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still playing dumb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.06,0:18:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because at that Vingt campaign—{Vingteland, Vingt-et-Un... really hard to tell here what she's saying, since it's fast/slurry.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Did you believe that I was thinking about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you saying you weren't...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.10,0:18:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.96,0:18:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.15,0:19:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kureha-chan made one too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.11,0:19:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not like I believe in souls or anything, though.{D'awww. Tsuntsun (´???`)}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.69,0:19:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my duty! Duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san, who are you sending off?{Can get elaborate here with okuru's many meanings}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Companions from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a lone unknown soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.66,0:19:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for the ones{lit: benefactor, perhaps use a synonym like angels for epicness, and cause they're.. dead? =D}{I would have went for angels, but i can't imagine that dead guy an angel...} who'd taught me many important things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could that person be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.13,0:19:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's anything troubling you, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I might not be of any use though...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.19,0:19:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I've made you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.11,0:19:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.56,0:19:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to worry about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.39,0:19:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san is always worrying about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If something is worrying you, then I want to worry about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.94,0:20:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I love you, Filicia-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.97,0:20:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you too, Kana-chan.{Les end GETTO!!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.00,0:20:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't change the way you are now.{lit is 'live without changing'}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.97,0:20:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.{Can be 'For me' 'I beg of you' Whatever floats your pronboat}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.39,0:20:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.10,0:20:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These heavy words won't be forgotten.{Lit heavy, serious, impotant}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.40,0:20:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's a great thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.26,0:20:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.66,0:20:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.49,0:20:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How adorable.{take kawaii for one of it's many non-standard meanings}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.47,0:21:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come again next year, my ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.27,0:21:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad... Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother... Sister...{Varying levels of respect if you want to make them different}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.68,0:21:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That person is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Rio, you asked me earlier if there was any meaning to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.28,0:21:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.27,0:21:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was the only one left alive, I thought about that for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.98,0:21:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why am I the only one still alive, and is there any meaning in that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.39,0:21:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.22,0:21:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there isn't any sort of meaning to this world.{Drop 'or anything' if you feel it's too much here, in English.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.41,0:22:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that still wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if there isn't one, then you can decide what it is for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.95,0:22:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.62,0:22:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.92,0:22:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.73,0:22:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was really scowling. Then Yumina-oneechan...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.76,0:22:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To definitely never let those children feel the same way I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.22,0:22:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:47.53,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let's remember our love and friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:47.53,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou omoikasanete
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.39,0:22:50.74,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}and play out their importance.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.39,0:22:50.74,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}taisetsu wo kanadeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:08.66,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}We were so happy that we cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:08.66,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}ureshikute naita
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.64,0:23:14.66,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}It hurt so much that we laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.64,0:23:14.66,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}itakute waratta
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.72,0:23:23.86,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}But these are all proof that we are alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.72,0:23:23.86,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}dakedo sonna zenbu ga ikiteru akashi nan desu
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.57,0:23:28.17,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let's move forward one step at a time.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.57,0:23:28.17,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}yukkuri aruite yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.67,0:23:29.63,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Everybody singing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:34.14,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let me hear the words of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:34.14,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}hitosashi no honne kikasete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.60,0:23:35.34,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}You're just my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.14,0:23:41.04,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Even if our love and friendship sometimes waver,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.14,0:23:41.04,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou toki ni yuretemo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:41.34,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}I know, you know, a little happy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.08,0:23:46.96,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}let's make it echo forever and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.08,0:23:46.96,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}zutto zutto hibiki aitai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.08,0:23:47.32,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you hear my precious note?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.05,0:23:53.30,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Words are hardly enough to describe it.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:47.05,0:23:53.30,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}arifureteru kotoba de wa tsutaekirenai
Dialogue: 1,0:23:53.01,0:23:59.10,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}This is our harmony.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:53.01,0:23:59.10,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}watashitachi no harmony
Dialogue: 2,0:23:59.00,0:24:04.13,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you hear it? Our harmony!
Dialogue: 3,0:23:59.00,0:24:04.13,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}kikoeru our harmony
